OL,5, For 98-year-old Lidiia Lomikovska,     
OL,6, Russia's invasion is worse than the    
OL,7, Second World War, which she also lived 
OL,8, through.                               
OL,10,FShe's learnt to trust her instincts.   
OL,12,FIt's why when Russian forces entered   
OL,13,Fher home village of Ocheretyne in      
OL,14,Feastern Ukraine, she and her family    
OL,15,Fdecided it was time to go.             
OL,17,FHowever, under heavy shelling, Lidiia  
OL,18,Fsoon became separated from her         
OL,19,Frelatives, so started walking west in  
OL,20,Fher slippers.                          
